   "source": [
    "## Part 1: The Gravitational Potential of the Earth\n",
    "----\n",
    "\n",
    "The gravitational potential at a distance $r$ from a mass $M$ is given by:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\Phi(r) = -\\frac{GM}{r}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where G is the gravitational constant."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ebb8322b-f2b6-414d-aa61-29c447bf995e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Code up a function that takes as an input the mass of a body $M$ , the cartesian location of the\n",
    "mass $(x_M , y_M)$, and the location of some distant evaluation point $(x, y)$. Have the function\n",
    "return the potential at the evaluation point. You may consider approximating the Earth as\n",
    "a point particle, but in which case, be careful! For in that approximation, the the potential\n",
    "contains a singularity. In our function, use all modern best practices for coding.\n",
    "E.g. type hints, type checks, pre and post conditions, doc strings, etc."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "71a8928d-345f-4c25-a40b-c5d4631618e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def Earth (G:float, M:float, xM:float, yM:float, x:float, y:float)-> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Arguments:\n",
    "    G(float): gravity can't be less than 0\n",
    "    M(float): mass\n",
    "    xM, yM (float): cartesian location of the mass\n",
    "    x,y (float): location of distant evaluation point\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    if not isinstance (G,(float,int)):\n",
    "        raise TypeError(f\"G must be a numerical value\")\n",
    "    elif G<=0:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f\"G should not be a value less than or equal to zero\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not isinstance (M,(float, int)):\n",
    "        raise TypeError(f\"M must be a numerical value\")\n",
    "    elif M<=0:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f\"M should not be a value less than or equal to zero\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not isinstance(xM, (float,int)):\n",
    "        raise TypeError(f\"xM must be a numerical value\")\n",
    "    if not isinstace(yM, (float,int)):\n",
    "        raise TypeError(f\"yM must be a numerical value\")\n",
    "    if not isinstance (x, (float,int)):\n",
    "        raise TypeError(f\"x must be a numerical value\")\n",
    "    if not isinstance (y,(float,int)):\n",
    "        raise TypeError(f\"y must be a numerical value\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    r=np.sqrt((x-xM)**2 + (y-yM)**2)\n",
    "    if r==0:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f\"gravitational potential can't have r=0\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    gravitational_potential= -G*M/r\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not np.isfinite(gravitational_potential):\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f\"gravitational potential must be finite\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    return gravitational_potential\n"
   ]
  },
