      "15.8\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#Using the time equation you plug-in the values from the chart for wet mass, burn rate, dry mass\n",
    "T= 15.8 #s\n",
    "print(T)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dc4985a1-8ae6-4e8d-88f0-9aba3b5bd1ba",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2. Define a function that returns the change in velocity $\\Delta v(t)$.\n",
    "It should take all necessary arguments, meaning: the time, \n",
    "wet mass, dry mass, burn rate, exhaust speed, and gravitational constant $g$. \n",
    "Have it return the change in velocity.\n",
    "Note that the rocket eventually runs out of fuel, \n",
    "so you should design your function carefully so that \n",
    "$\\Delta v$ eventually becomes zero after all fuel is spent.\n",
    "Again, document and guard your function according to best practices."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "007d9cee-ff56-4eca-a134-9f2ba46a28ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "t= 15.8 #s\n",
    "m_o= 2.8e6 #kg\n",
    "m_f=7.5e5 #kg\n",
    "g=9.8 #m/s^2\n",
    "v_e= 2.4e3 #m/s\n",
    "def velocity(t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "   t= time a float or integer\n",
    "   m_o= float or integer, wet mass\n",
    "   m_f= float or integer, dry mass of rocket when all of the fuel is burned out\n",
    "   g= float, constant, 9.8 m/s^2\n",
    "   m= float or integer, burn fuel rate\n",
    "   v_e= float or intege, fuel exhaust velocity\n",
    "       \"\"\"\n",
    "    m_t= m_o-m*t\n",
    "    return  v_e*np.log(m_o/m_t)-g*t #change in velocity\n",
    "    \n"
   ]
